analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Population
analysisPopulations.text: The safety population will include any subject who: 1. receives 1 dose of any of the following: 20vPnC, 13vPnC, PPSV23, or saline; and 2. has safety follow-up after any vaccination.
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The safety population will include any subject who: 1. receives 1 dose of any of the following: 20vPnC, 13vPnC, PPSV23, or saline; and 2. has safety follow-up after any vaccination.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received 1 dose of study vaccine/saline AND has safety follow-up

analysisPopulations.name: Evaluable 13-Matched Immunogenicity Population – Cohort 1
analysisPopulations.text: Subjects in Cohort 1 who are included in the vaccine group as randomized and meet specific evaluability criteria for the 13 serotypes matched between 20vPnC and 13vPnC.
analysisPopulations.label: Evaluable 13-Matched
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Subjects in Cohort 1 who are included in the vaccine group as randomized and meet specific evaluability criteria for the 13 serotypes matched between 20vPnC and 13vPnC.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Cohort 1 AND randomized vaccine group AND met evaluability criteria for 13 matched serotypes

analysisPopulations.name: Evaluable 7-Additional Immunogenicity Population – Cohort 1
analysisPopulations.text: Subjects in Cohort 1 who are included in the vaccine group as randomized and meet specific evaluability criteria for the 7 additional serotypes in 20vPnC compared to 13vPnC.
analysisPopulations.label: Evaluable 7-Additional
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Subjects in Cohort 1 who are included in the vaccine group as randomized and meet specific evaluability criteria for the 7 additional serotypes in 20vPnC compared to 13vPnC.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Cohort 1 AND randomized vaccine group AND met evaluability criteria for 7 additional serotypes

analysisPopulations.name: Evaluable Immunogenicity Population for Comparison of Cohorts 2 and 3 to Cohort 1
analysisPopulations.text: Subjects in Cohorts 2 and 3, and the comparison group in Cohort 1, who are included in the vaccine group as randomized and meet specific evaluability criteria for the 20 serotypes.
analysisPopulations.label: Evaluable-20
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Subjects in Cohorts 2 and 3, and the comparison group in Cohort 1, who are included in the vaccine group as randomized and meet specific evaluability criteria for the 20 serotypes.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized vaccine group AND met evaluability criteria for 20 serotypes

characteristics.name: Age
characteristics.description: Age at vaccination at Visit 1 in years, derived based on the subject’s birthday.

characteristics.name: Race
characteristics.description: Black/African American, American Indian or Alaskan native, Asian, Native Hawaiian or other Pacific Islander, white, or multiracial.

characteristics.name: Medical History
characteristics.description: Underlying medical conditions or risk factors categorized according to MedDRA.
